#. <section class="sutta" id="sn48.37"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn48.37:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 48"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 48"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.37:0.2"
msgid "4. Sukhindriyavagga"
msgstr "4. The Pleasure Faculty"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn48.37:0.3"
msgid "37. Dutiyavibhaṅgasutta"
msgstr "37. Analysis (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.37:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, indriyāni."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five faculties."

msgctxt "sn48.37:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn48.37:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sukhindriyaṃ, dukkhindriyaṃ, somanassindriyaṃ, domanassindriyaṃ, "
"upekkhindriyaṃ."
msgstr "The faculties of pleasure, pain, happiness, sadness, and equanimity."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.210"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.37:2.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, sukhindriyaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the faculty of pleasure?"

msgctxt "sn48.37:2.2"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, kāyikaṃ sukhaṃ, kāyikaṃ sātaṃ, kāyasamphassajaṃ sukhaṃ "
"sātaṃ vedayitaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Physical enjoyment, physical pleasure, the enjoyable, pleasant feeling that’"
"s born from physical contact."

msgctxt "sn48.37:2.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sukhindriyaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the faculty of pleasure."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.37:3.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, dukkhindriyaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the faculty of pain?"

msgctxt "sn48.37:3.2"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, kāyikaṃ dukkhaṃ, kāyikaṃ asātaṃ, kāyasamphassajaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ asātaṃ vedayitaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Physical pain, physical displeasure, the painful, unpleasant feeling that’s "
"born from physical contact."

msgctxt "sn48.37:3.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhindriyaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the faculty of pain."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.37:4.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, somanassindriyaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the faculty of happiness?"

msgctxt "sn48.37:4.2"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, cetasikaṃ sukhaṃ, cetasikaṃ sātaṃ, manosamphassajaṃ "
"sukhaṃ sātaṃ vedayitaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Mental enjoyment, mental pleasure, the enjoyable, pleasant feeling that’s "
"born from mind contact."

msgctxt "sn48.37:4.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, somanassindriyaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the faculty of happiness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.37:5.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, domanassindriyaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the faculty of sadness?"

msgctxt "sn48.37:5.2"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, cetasikaṃ dukkhaṃ, cetasikaṃ asātaṃ, manosamphassajaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ asātaṃ vedayitaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Mental pain, mental displeasure, the painful, unpleasant feeling that’s born "
"from mind contact."

msgctxt "sn48.37:5.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, domanassindriyaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the faculty of sadness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.37:6.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, upekkhindriyaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the faculty of equanimity?"

msgctxt "sn48.37:6.2"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, kāyikaṃ vā cetasikaṃ vā nevasātaṃ nāsātaṃ vedayitaṃ—"
msgstr "Neither pleasant nor unpleasant feeling, whether physical or mental."

msgctxt "sn48.37:6.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, upekkhindriyaṃ."
msgstr "This is the faculty of equanimity."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.37:7.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yañca sukhindriyaṃ yañca somanassindriyaṃ, sukhā sā vedanā "
"daṭṭhabbā."
msgstr ""
"In this context, the faculties of pleasure and happiness should be seen as "
"pleasant feeling."

msgctxt "sn48.37:7.2"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yañca dukkhindriyaṃ yañca domanassindriyaṃ, dukkhā sā "
"vedanā daṭṭhabbā."
msgstr "The faculties of pain and sadness should be seen as painful feeling."

msgctxt "sn48.37:7.3"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yadidaṃ upekkhindriyaṃ, adukkhamasukhā sā vedanā daṭṭhabbā."
msgstr "The faculty of equanimity should be seen as neutral feeling."

msgctxt "sn48.37:7.4"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañcindriyānī”ti."
msgstr "These are the five faculties.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn48.37:7.5"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
